title: Web3 Hackathon
subtitle: Australia, May - Aug 2023
text: The Web3 Hackathon was Australia's premier annual hackathon event catered to a global audience, supporting the next generation of Web3 innovation and products. As part of the AI + Web3 Convention, W3C hosted a web3 hackathon for students from May 15th to Aug 18, 2023, with over $100k in grants and prizes. Students and recent alumni from all universities were welcomed to participate. W3C believed in nurturing enthusiastic builders of the future. The University web3 hackathon gave students a chance to build and showcase their projects for a chance to claim grants and prizes valued at over $100k.
